sentences: Ta on fotol väga loomulik välja tulnud.
Loomulik valgus ja õhuvahetus on vajalik tervisele.
Eelistab naiste loomulikku ilu meigi abil saavutatule.
context: The Estonian adjective 'loomulik' means natural, inherent, normal or expected. It describes something that conforms to nature, is characteristic of someone's inherent qualities, or happens in the usual/ordinary way without being forced or artificial. The word can refer to physical characteristics (natural appearance), behaviors (inherent tendencies), processes (normal development), or phenomena (expected consequences).
